1. Project:

        This program have been developed by the IMAGO Research
        Group since 2001. The goal is to create novel applications
        using simple ideas.

        http://www.inf.ufpr.br/imago/mouseloupe
 
        Coordinator: Prof. Dr. Luciano Silva at the
        Undergraduate students: Fabio Leite Vieira, Mauricley Ribas
                                Azevedo e Thiago de Souza Ferreira
	Collaborators: Profa. Dra. Olga Regina Pereira Bellon
		       Prof.Dr. Alexandre Ibrahim Direne
		       

2. Instalation:

	Download the source code from IMAGO website or sourceforge.net

	Run:
              tar -xvjf mouseloupe_v0.6.tar.bz2
	      cd mouseloupe
              make
              make install


3. Documentation:

        On-line manual: man mouseloupe
             

4. Dependences:
	
	To compile the mouseloupe it is necessary to have X11R6.8
        from X.org and to enable the Composite extension. 
 
        To enable the Composite extension you must include the
        following lines in your xorg.conf file and restart your xserver
		
	# *********************************
	# Extensions section
	# *********************************

	Section "Extensions"
		Option "Composite" "Enable"
	EndSection


5. Running the mouseloupe:

	mouseloupe &
	    
	     or
 
        If you have Tcl/Tk installed:
	
	mouseloupegui &
	
	
6. Known bugs:

	- crash when using nedit (version 5.5)
        - stop working when other aplications menu pop-up
        
	
